job_title: Sr Director, Data Science and Analytics
job_Description: Our Opportunity:      Chewy is hiring a  Senior Director, Marketing Analytics & Data Science  for our Marketing Science & Operations team in one of our three campuses in Dania Beach, FL, Boston, MA, or Seattle, WA. Our mission is to build world-class analytics, data science & technology organization that supports and connects all marketing endeavors across internal and external stakeholders/platforms.      The team uses business economics, statistics, and machine learning techniques to understand and serve the needs of our pet parents. Developing data-driven marketing solutions, we are an interdisciplinary team of analysts and data scientists committed to solving business problems using cutting-edge technologies and developing data-driven marketing solutions.      This leadership position will have exposure across the entire business, influencing the heart of Chewy's marketing efforts, directly impacting an annual marketing budget of $xxxM, which drives our corporate growth. Committed to value-creation, you will work with cross-functional stakeholders, including Marketing, Merchandising, and Finance, as a thought leader and guide them in their decision-making process using data as your north star. This position will include the following areas of coverage:               Develop analytical frameworks to address business opportunities across our customer journey, customer behaviors, lifecycle segments, and merchandising categories (Consumables, Hardgoods, Healthcare, etc.)               Surface growth opportunities and validating hypotheses through experimentation, measurement, statistical methods, and machine learning models.               Support our Marketing Measurement Science function – this function is committed to developing data-driven solutions, advancing measurement capabilities, building optimization frameworks, establishing best practices. Furthermore, they will identify growth opportunities across marketing channels, using marketing mix modeling (MMM), testing/experimentation, attribution, causal inference, forecasting, 3rd party solutions, etc.               Develop our customer science function responsible for continuously expanding our customer lifetime value frameworks using causal inference methods to bring precision and speed in the decision-making process. Additionally, they will develop propensity scoring modeling to access the best action for Chewy to personalize the message for each of its customers.             What you'll do:          Hire, develop and lead a team of data scientists, statisticians and analysts.      Identify and manage priorities within the context of overall Chewy objectives, and work with data science and engineering colleagues to drive the best practices in developing, testing, and producing models at scale.      Establish strong working relationships at all organizational levels across different functional teams.      Focusing on the incrementality and the value-creation in everything you do, you will closely work with the stakeholders within the Marketing and Finance teams. You will transform their ideas, preliminary findings, or analyses, whenever applicable, into machine learning-driven business strategies, programs, and actions that would help drive the core objectives. For such transformations, you will guide the teams with the design of experiments, measurements, analyses, and recommendations.      You will set the strategic direction for the data science and analytics teams as they build programs to tackle marketing business problems. Current approaches include but are not limited to media mix modeling, cross-channel spend optimization, multi-touch attribution, propensity, incremental lift, causal inference, structural equation modeling, etc.      You will use data to improve how we make decisions and ultimately enhance customer experience and drive loyalty.      You will work with the data engineering teams to develop the automated pipelines to perform different stages of the model life cycle (data collection and cleaning, model development and validation, model deployment and scoring, periodic validation and refitting, etc.)         What you'll need:          Graduate degree (MS/Ph.D./MBA) or comparable experience in Data Science, Machine Learning, Economics, Statistics, Mathematics, Engineering, or highly related quantitative discipline with 8+ years of working experience in the industry, consulting, agency, or academic research.      Have 8+ years of professional experience in product management, data science, or applied economics, of which 5+ years as a people leader.      Track record of building and nurturing teams of data scientists, analysts, statisticians, or economists.      Preferably experience of working in marketing analytics and measurement fields, with domain knowledge and familiarity in marketing channels (both digital and mass media such as TV measurement), marketing performance KPIs, marketing advertising platforms (e.g., Google, Facebook, CTV, TV), and marketing analytics tools (e.g., Google Analytics, Ads Data Hub, etc.).      Preferably has experience in attribution, spend optimization, incrementality testing, etc.      Possesses excellent verbal and written communication skills with the ability to explain complex concepts to non-experts in a simple, understandable way.      Working knowledge of AWS data toolset (e.g., Amazon SageMaker, S3) is a plus.      Can work in a fast-paced environment and be persuasive and caring with a wide range of diverse, cross-cultural audiences.      Ability to thrive in complex business environments defined by uncertain, incomplete, or limited information and evolving targets. Comfortable finding (or building) common ground to drive their agenda.      Strong at operating under constraints and prioritizing time-sensitive deliveries.      Preferably has experience in the e-commerce industry.            Chewy is committed to equal opportunity. We value and embrace diversity and inclusion of all Team Members.                If you have a disability under the Americans with Disabilities Act or similar law, or you require a religious accommodation, and you wish to discuss potential accommodations related to applying for employment at Chewy, please contact  HR@chewy.com .                To access Chewy’s Privacy Policy, which contains information regarding information collected from job applicants and how we use it, please click here:  https://www.chewy.com/app/content/privacy ).

UnitedHealth Group is a company that's on the rise. We're expanding in multiple directions, across borders and, most of all, in the way we think. Here, innovation isn't about another gadget, it's about transforming the health care industry. Ready to make a difference? Make yourself at home with us and start doing  your life's best work.(sm)      Optum Labs is the research and development arm of UnitedHealth Group. We're a diverse team of curious thinkers and experts in big data, artificial intelligence and machine learning, and scientific and clinical research searching for new ways to help people live healthier lives. We partner with world leaders in health care delivery, research, and technology to create disruptive solutions that serve patients, caregivers, providers, and commercial and government payers.     More equitable, effective, and affordable health care - that's our goal. We aren't just trying to improve the care an individual receives. We're building a future where the health care system works better for everyone.      You’ll enjoy the flexibility to telecommute* from anywhere within the U.S. as you take on some tough challenges.      Primary Responsibilities:           The Director of Research designs and executes on a portfolio of research studies to explore how to advance the quadruple aim through strategic use of genetic testing in healthcare delivery. The Director is responsible for oversight and conduct of research of the highest quality. Work is conducted in a collaborative, multi-disciplinary, academic/industry partnership environment which requires appreciation of diversity of perspectives and excellent communication skills. Energetic leadership, creative thinking, and internal drive are a must. We hire talented people for challenging jobs and expect a high level of independence and adaptability.       Provide senior consultation to client organizations on fit-for-purpose research designs to achieve strategic objectives       Lead proposal development       Design and oversee execution of studies and research projects       Develop collaborative relationships with internal and external experts to support the research agenda       Advance dissemination of results via published manuscripts, professional conferences, and internal presentations       Support identification and acquisition of specific data resources and technologies required to support a research agenda       Oversee project teams and manage study timelines       Mentor and train new research staff as needed            You’ll be rewarded and recognized for your performance in an environment that will challenge you and give you clear direction on what it takes to succeed in your role as well as provide development for other roles you may be interested in.      Required Qualifications:           Master’s degree in health services research (HSR), health economics, epidemiology, sociology, psychology or equivalent, or PharmD or MD       8+ years of healthcare economics and outcomes research (HEOR) experience       8+ years of research experience with claims data, EHR, and other observational data assets       Experience conducting health economics, epidemiological, comparative effectiveness, population management, or related research in various disease or policy areas       Established record of independently designing, leading, and conducting HEOR) projects       Demonstrated experience in data-driven research       Record of publication in peer-reviewed literature and presentation at national conferences       Demonstrated experience managing all aspects of HEOR projects including management of teams across multiple functional areas       Full COVID-19 vaccination is an essential requirement of this role. Candidates located in states that mandate COVID-19 booster doses must also comply with those state requirements. UnitedHealth Group will adhere to all federal, state and local regulations as well as all client requirements and will obtain necessary proof of vaccination, and boosters when applicable, prior to employment to ensure compliance          Preferred Qualifications:           PhD in health services research (HSR), health economics, epidemiology, sociology, psychology or equivalent, or PharmD or MD       Experience designing research studies involving collection of patient-reported outcomes using survey research methodologies       Expertise in a specific therapeutic area (e.g., oncology, cardio-metabolic, rare disease)       Exceptional written and oral communication skills, particularly to audiences of varying skill levels       Solid interpersonal savvy and the ability to build relationships both internally and outside the enterprise          TRAVEL: Post-COVID, travel is required for this role and varies throughout the year (largely centered around external research partners and conference presentations) - less than 10%      WE LEAD WITH DIVERSITY, INCLUSION AND COMPASSION   At Optum Labs, we are dedicated to building teams where every individual is recognized for their unique experience and contributions. Our Leadership Principles underscore our commitment to inclusion, encouraging us to “walk in each other’s shoes” and open doors for our peers.      UnitedHealth Group supports local, regional, and national organizations that share these values through joint initiatives, event and program participation, volunteerism and giving. Through our Connected Communities, employees can connect with others who have similar – or different – life experiences and backgrounds. These groups are led by peers, supported by Human Capital, and championed by leaders.      WE INVEST IN TALENT   Managers at every level are committed to their roles as talent stewards who help guide and nurture professional development. We want our employees to reach their highest level of potential just as they help us reach ours.      At Optum Labs, employees are our first customers. That’s why we offer virtual work environments – to provide work/life flexibility via telecommuting. While it can be a struggle to be a telecommuter, it can also provide enormous benefits for your personal and professional life.      Sources:   https://careers.unitedhealthgroup.com/culture/what-we-offer/   https://careers.unitedhealthgroup.com/culture/life-at-uhg/   https://hub.uhg.com/news/2021-3-10-Introducing-Connected-Communities- 503662/5744    https://careers.unitedhealthgroup.com/culture/inclusion-and-diversity/      UnitedHealth Group requires all new hires and employees to report their COVID-19 vaccination status.           To protect the health and safety of our workforce, patients and communities we serve, UnitedHealth Group and its affiliate companies require all employees to disclose COVID-19 vaccination status prior to beginning employment. In addition, some roles and locations require full COVID-19 vaccination, including boosters, as an essential job function. UnitedHealth Group adheres to all federal, state and local COVID-19 vaccination regulations as well as all client COVID-19 vaccination requirements and will obtain the necessary information from candidates prior to employment to ensure compliance. Candidates must be able to perform all essential job functions with or without reasonable accommodation. Failure to meet the vaccination requirement may result in rescission of an employment offer or termination of employment.      Careers at UnitedHealth Group.  We have modest goals: Improve the lives of others. Change the landscape of health care forever. Leave the world a better place than we found it. Such aspirations tend to attract a certain type of person. Crazy talented. Compassionate. Driven. To these select few, we offer the global reach, resources and can-do culture of a Fortune 5 company. We provide an environment where you're empowered to be your best. We encourage you to take risks. And we offer a world of rewards and benefits for performance. We believe the most important is the opportunity to do  your life's best work.(sm)      Colorado, Connecticut or Nevada Residents Only:  The salary range for Colorado residents is $134,200 to $257,700. The salary range for Connecticut / Nevada residents is $134,200 to $257,700. Pay is based on several factors including but not limited to education, work experience, certifications, etc. In addition to your salary, UnitedHealth Group offers benefits such as, a comprehensive benefits package, incentive and recognition programs, equity stock purchase and 401k contribution (all benefits are subject to eligibility requirements). No matter where or when you begin a career with UnitedHealth Group, you’ll find a far-reaching choice of benefits and incentives.      *All Telecommuters will be required to adhere to UnitedHealth Group’s Telecommuter Policy.           Diversity creates a healthier atmosphere: UnitedHealth Group is an Equal Employment Opportunity/Affirmative Action employer and all qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, age, national origin, protected veteran status, disability status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, marital status, genetic information, or any other characteristic protected by law. job_title: Senior Data Scientist - Machine Learning & AI
job_Description: Calabrio is looking for an experienced Senior Data Scientist with a strong background in applied mathematics and statistics, to contribute to and grow our Calabrio Machine Learning and AI practice. Using large quantities of omnichannel contact center-generated data (numerical, text, audio, behavioral, and user-generated data), the person in this role will focus on prototyping innovative solutions designed to revolutionize the contact center and customer experience industries.            As a Senior Data Scientist, you’ll be researching, experimenting, applying various techniques, and looking for novel approaches to the problems at hand. You will also be developing working prototypes to assess the viability of the approaches while implementing the solution that can be deployed into production. Data Scientists at Calabrio have close relationships with the product development teams and serve as the technical aid in generating ideas for innovative features in the Calabrio software suite. This is an ideal role for a Machine Learning and AI professional with a true passion for research and experimentation who craves high visibility and impact, while working with cutting-edge technologies. A background in independent research and experience in experimental design.      Ability to transform “raw” data to conform to the assumptions of a machine learning algorithm.                  Nice to Haves:         Master’s degree or PhD strongly preferred      Strong proficiency in Python and related technologies such as TensorFlow & Pytorch.      Deep knowledge of computer science, math, probability, statistics, and algorithms preferred        Benefits     Calabrio People are: Open, Clear, Ambitious, Accountable, Collaborative, Consistent     What we value most…workplace diversity and ensuring an environment of mutual respect. Our commitment is to continue to keep our people healthy, focused, and creative. We've built a company culture where you’ll feel motivated and truly excited to come to work. As an equal opportunity employer, we always consider and embrace ALL individuals including what makes them unique. We believe our team members should be happy and healthy, with peace of mind and a sense of accomplishment. Our team members are offered comprehensive benefits for various life circumstances and needs, great opportunities for career development, and a balanced work-life to achieve personal and professional success (all benefits are subject to eligibility requirements). job_title: Data & AI Solution Area Leader-Midwest Region
job_Description: About the role: Solution Areas are what we want to be known for in the market; they are the areas on which our clients most frequently seek our guidance during their digital transformation journey. Within our Solution Areas, we have core Offerings, which are the solutions we deliver to our clients. By specializing in and formalizing these select Offerings, we can deepen our relationships with our clients across their entire business and compete in new areas, helping us to grow our market share. Using the power of modern data platforms, visualizations, advanced analytics, machine learning, IOT/Digital Twins and applied intelligence, we help clients gain business insights to optimize their operations, drive innovation, and make more empowered decisions. As a regional Data & AI Solution Area Lead, you will lead and guide the Data & AI Solution Area business for your region. You will be responsible for the overall strategy, performance and growth of the Data & AI offerings in your assigned geography. You will partner across our consulting, Center of Excellence and other solution area teams to create cutting edge solutions to address our clients’ needs. You will work with our marquis industry partners (Accenture & Microsoft) to support regional sales and delivery teams through the full lifecycle of solution development and execution. You will work within diverse teams of professionals at varying levels to ensure a carefully manage sales and delivery process resulting in successful client engagements! As a Regional Solution Area Lead you will,  Continue to identify the most relevant cross-industry solutions-at-scale for your region and execute on them including Data Migration, Automation Migration, Visualization/Reporting and Core Data Platform Modernization and Governance  Build and lead the strategy execution for Avanade’s Applied Intelligence, IOT/Digital Twin, Industry X (industry 4.0) and Intelligent Automation businesses in your region  Drive measurable and sustained growth across the Data & AI Solution Area  Integrate Data & AI into the other Global Solution Areas (Modern Workplace, Apps & Infrastructure, and Business Applications), offerings and go-to-market initiatives  Drive strong Managed Services and multi-year engagements for Data & AI  Be known for your "client centric" approach and delivery excellence  Champion differentiated commercial models and outcomes for our clients with a focus on client value, and longer term and stronger client relationships  Drive sales and delivery utilizing a Global network and leveraging offshore and near-shore sales, solutioning, and delivery capabilities  Effectively partner with our parent companies Accenture and Microsoft and other ISVs  Lead with a strong orientation and focus on the development of your team with an elevation in diversity  As a Data & AI leader, you will contribute to the development of the annual regional business plan and budgets through both strategies and actions. Through the gathering of marketplace and cross regional insights, you’ll shape requirements for solution offerings, while setting the tone for effective delivery of projects, including delivery innovations and enhancement suggestions to improve overall efficiency.  Day-to-day, you will:   Drive customer conversations and business outcomes  Effectively architect and solution with clients and drive sales through proposal to deal closing  Partner with Accenture and Microsoft leadership to develop the alliance and identify and close business opportunities. Location: US (Remote) or Canada (Remote)                   As a Senior Applied Researcher – Machine Learning within the PointClickCare Advanced Technology team, you will work with customers, product leaders, subject matter experts, other highly experienced applied researchers, engineers, or others on cutting-edge research and development projects to address the needs of users in the acute, post-acute, long term and cross-continuum care space to truly transform healthcare.                  Examples of typical project areas and responsibilities include end to end responsibilities for developing, improving, and validating new machine learning models, working with other researchers to improve and validate the performance of machine learning models, and working with engineers on infrastructure to support the automated deployment and management of models or incorporating models into large scale commercial SaaS products. Responsibilities :              Perform research, experimentation, and related engineering to design, build and evaluate machine learning-based models to be deployed into production environments,       Tasks may include (for example) data collection, data cleaning, data analysis, model training, development, and evaluation, and scaling up the system. Strong interest in applying machine learning to healthcare-related problems and data. PwC’s Cloud Computing and Networking practice helps our clients transform their business through innovative technology solutions and effective IT Service Management. Part of that journey includes helping our clients enable innovation, reinventing their customer experience, and exploring new markets. You will be immersed in a variety of different projects, groups, and locations while getting inspired through your community to grow as an individual as well as a team. Our diverse client service teams encourages out-of-the-box thinking, problem solving, great team mentality and a curiosity for understanding the latest in technology. To really stand out and make us fit for the future in a constantly changing world, each and every one of us at PwC needs to be a purpose-led and values-driven leader at every level. To help us achieve this we have the PwC Professional; our global leadership development framework. It gives us a single set of expectations across our lines, geographies and career paths, and provides transparency on the skills we need as individuals to be successful and progress in our careers, now and in the future. As a Manager, you'll work as part of a team of problem solvers, helping to solve complex business issues from strategy to execution. PwC Professional skills and responsibilities for this management level include but are not limited to: Develop new skills outside of comfort zone. Act to resolve issues which prevent the team working effectively. Coach others, recognise their strengths, and encourage them to take ownership of their personal development. Analyse complex ideas or proposals and build a range of meaningful recommendations. Use multiple sources of information including broader stakeholder views to develop solutions and recommendations. Address sub-standard work or work that does not meet firm's/client's expectations. Use data and insights to inform conclusions and support decision-making. Develop a point of view on key global trends, and how they impact clients. Manage a variety of viewpoints to build consensus and create positive outcomes for all parties. Simplify complex messages, highlighting and summarising key points. Uphold the firm's code of ethics and business conduct. Additional Job Description Job Requirements and Preferences :   Basic Qualifications :   Minimum Degree Required : Bachelor Degree   Minimum Years of Experience : 5 year(s)   Preferred Qualifications :   Certification(s) Preferred : Certification from a leading cloud or service management provider   Preferred Knowledge/Skills : Demonstrates extensive-level abilities and success with managing the identification and addressing of client needs. As a Manager, you have extensive level abilities understanding of one or both of the following areas: Working with cloud platforms and the technologies that make them work. (AWS, Azure, Google Cloud Platform); and, Working with IT Service Management and how it is implemented across different operating models. (ITIL, ServiceNow). Demonstrates extensive abilities and/or a proven record of success in the following areas: Bringing together the right perspectives, identify roadblocks, and integrate feedback from clients and team members; Managing delivery from project scoping to conclusion, while consistently keeping the client’s goals in mind; Having a passion for developing and growing team members; Communicating complex information simply; Finding yourself in the role of advisor and peer to others; Approaching new projects with an open mind; Believing empathy for coworkers and customers is key to your success; Valuing learning from mistakes and ask for help when needed; Persevering through challenges; Believing in the value created by diverse teams and can adapt to a variety of working styles; and, Developing thought leadership materials to further your knowledge and create new relationships. Demonstrates extensive abilities and/or a proven record of success in the following areas: Cloud Platforms (Amazon Web Services (AWS), Azure, GCP); Cloud Strategy, Design, Architecture and Migration; DevOps, Automation CI/CI; AI, Machine Learning, IoT; ServiceNow, Remedy (Helix); ITIL, COBIT; Service Catalogue, CMDB; and, Incident, Problem and Change Management. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment at PwC without regard to race; creed; color; religion; national origin; sex; age; disability; sexual orientation; gender identity or expression; genetic predisposition or carrier status; veteran, marital, or citizenship status; or any other status protected by law. Backed by Sequoia Capital, Nvidia, Great Hill Partners, Coatue Management, and Bloomberg Beta, we are at the epicenter of the data science revolution, helping companies develop the next breakthrough in medicine, build better cars, or recommend the best song play next. Our Sales Engineers work closely with Enterprise Account Executives to conduct product demonstrations, design and execute successful proof-of-concepts, and determine the technical needs for customer implementations. Domino is a nimble, growing company and as such the Sales Engineers work closely with Marketing, Product Management, and Engineering to help vivify the market's needs. pre-sales strongly preferred    Outstanding verbal and written communication skills    Excellent presentation skills, both web and in-person    Comfortable scripting, preferably in python    Experience working with cloud platforms such as AWS, GCP, Azure, etc.    Linux Systems Administration    Working knowledge with Docker and Kubernetes    Understanding of Data Science & Machine Learning concepts and AI/ML toolkits; some hands-on experience with data science languages, platforms, and/or toolkits strongly preferred    Hands-on experience working with Spark, Kafka, and/or NoSQL platforms    Comfortable with traveling to multiple customer locations when Covid conditions change (30% travel)     What we offer      Competitive compensation, commission, and equity package    Medical/Dental/Vision benefits for both you and your dependents    401k Retirement Plan    Flexible time off and paid parental leave    Open office with access to company leaders and tools for remote employees to stay connected    Opportunity to work with passionate people in a mission-driven company     Job Type: Full-time

About Us:    Our mission is to elevate leading brands through unforgettable digital connections with their customers. Sitecore delivers a composable digital experience platform that empowers the world’s smartest and largest brands to build lifelong relationships with their customers. A highly decorated industry leader, Sitecore is the leading company bringing together content, commerce, and data into one connected platform that delivers millions of digital experiences every day. Thousands of blue-chip companies including American Express, Porsche, Starbucks, L’Oréal, and Volvo Cars rely on Sitecore to provide more engaging, personalized experiences for their customers. Learn more at Sitecore.com.     Sitecore’s foundation is our diverse group of passionate, smart, innovative, and collaborative individuals located across four continents and over 25 countries. Having a wide range of perspectives, experiences, and skills is what makes us the company we are today. The Sitecore values are what drive and unite us across the globe. Sitecore is experiencing spectacular growth all over the world.     Position Overview:         Developing long-term vision and strategy for differentiated content search and personalization experiences using AI and machine learning      Lead with a strong background in SaaS solutions and customer journeys from prospect to purchase and support      Working collaboratively with product marketing, pricing and corporate marketing teams to develop marketing plans, positioning, core messaging, presentations, demos and sales tools to support the launch of new products with customers.      Manage a team of product owners to deliver the vision, with some HR responsibilities         What you will do         Engaging with both product users and product buyers to understand market problems and identify product opportunities.      Determine the required functionality to be enabled, built and tested to address market opportunities and user needs.      Collaborating with the engineering team or teams by providing clear feature specifications and business context, in conjunction with technical dependencies.      Manage a set of product owners and establish a cadence of leadership to deliver your vision      Strategic roadmap planning and dependency mapping as part of an overall product delivery program.      Respond to questions from sales RFPs and participate in customer calls with Sales Engineers and Technical Services when required.      Work with internal stakeholders across the company to communicate our value proposition.      Delivering Demos, Presentations and Workshops for key stakeholders in the business.        What you will need to succeed         BS degree or higher in Computer Science.      At least 2 years software engineering experience, or 3 years of product management experience in the SaaS space.      Strong analytical, troubleshooting, and problem-solving skills.      Comfortable with cloud-native technologies and working in a fast-paced and fast-changing environment.      High attention to detail including proven ability to manage multiple, competing priorities simultaneously.      Excellent communication skills (presentation, verbal and written).      Experience in machine learning, A/B testing, and analytics.        Additional Skills That Could Set You Apart:         Prior experience in content marketing is a plus      Experience in Internationalization/Localization is a plus.      Experience managing products in B2B environments is a plus.      MBA or advanced technical degree.        Why you should click ‘Apply’:         Growth!  We are tapping into an exciting $30B market opportunity that is still very much in its infancy and feel. It’s never been a better time to join Sitecore as we look to grow by 30% YoY. This engineering management role is an opportunity for a technologist with a passion for Linux and Ubuntu to build a career with Canonical and drive the success of the business. If you have an affinity for open source development, then you will enjoy working with some of the best people in the industry at Canonical.  Our new Commercial Systems unit is conceived as five engineering teams that closely collaborate with other engineering and business teams at Canonical. Services designed, developed, and operated by the Commercial Systems unit are used by millions of machines all over the world. Apply here if you would like to run one of these teams. They cover the following areas:  A contracts service.  We develop and operate a contracts service that, among others, supports the authentication, authorization, and delivery of Extended Security Maintenance (ESM) at scale to a wide range of devices spanning from individual systems to large enterprise fleets running in cloud environments via Ubuntu Advantage. This service also delivers certain contract-based services, like our kernel live patches.  JAAS/Identity/LivePatch . We take the operational scalability of Juju, Canonical's solution to public, private, and hybrid-cloud application management and orchestration, to the next level by developing JIMM (Juju Intelligent Model Manager) and Candid (open source identity manager) that enable organizations to operate clusters of Juju-enabled clouds at a scale. In addition to that, we deliver the LivePatch client package and the LivePatch server backend that integrate with the contracts service to deliver live patches for the Linux kernel.  Data lake and SAAS integration.  The third major area is related to internal business operations. We develop and operate several data warehouses, including data ingestion pipelines, used by operations and data analytics teams. In addition to that, we help internal business units to automate processes across a number of software solutions and integrate with a number of SaaS solutions to ensure a smooth flow of data.  Integration with public clouds.  The fourth major area or responsibility lies in integrating the contracts service with public clouds, such as Azure, AWS, and GCP, to deliver customers a seamless SAAS experience at the OS level, including access to Extended Security Maintenance and support offerings provided by Canonical personnel.  Salesforce . The fifth major area is centered around Salesforce. Our team of Salesforce engineers and administrators ensures that business operations teams have the right data at a hand and the right business processes in place. The team works closely with the four engineering teams and provides subject matter expertise.  We are looking for software engineering managers, ideally with strong background in Go or Python, who have the drive and energy to lead a team of engineers in delivering and operating these capabilities at scale, ensure the highest engineering quality, sharpen team skills, and work with us to define the future of open source.  We expect you to have  Bachelor's degree or equivalent in Computer Science or a related engineering field.  Experience as a software developer in a high-level language - preferably Go or Python.  Experience as a hands-on engineering manager or a team lead.  Experience building, deploying, and operating distributed systems and APIs.  Excellent verbal and written communication skills in English.  Ability to collaborate remotely with a diverse set of team members and stakeholders, remain highly motivated, productive, and organized in a fully remote environment.  Ability to travel to international destinations for one week at a time, approximately 2-4 times per year. Locations prior to the global pandemic included New York, Seattle, London, Cape Town, Budapest, Berlin, Montreal, and Brussels.  Nice to have  Experience developing for and deploying on Ubuntu Linux in public clouds.  Experience integrating authentication & authorization, financial, public cloud or marketplace systems.  Experience with Salesforce development/integration or APEX.  We offer  Learning and development opportunities and personal budget  Annual compensation review  Recognition rewards  Annual leave  Priority pass for travel   We are proud to foster a workplace free of discrimination. Diversity of experience, perspectives, and background create a better work environment and better products.  Whatever your identity  we will give your application fair consideration.  #LI-Remote  #stack

Director Marketing Data & Performance Analytics  We have embarked on a fantastic journey to connect Jostens with consumers to provide easy access to the brand and our product offerings that help everyone celebrate their special achievements. Our CEO and the Jostens Leadership Team are all “in” to create a harmonized omnichannel strategy that brings digital and physical touchpoints together to magnify our awareness with consumers while delivering a phenomenal end-to-end experience across the customer’s journey. Drive the digital analytics and customer intelligence program for the organization.  Harness data across multiple sources such as web/mobile and behavioral data, CRM and offline data sources, and transactional systems.  Identify critical moments within customer journey that can be enhanced using personas and segmentation to improve experiences and conversion.  Improve marketing impact by driving growth-conversion, retention and loyalty, and reducing customer acquisition costs and improve decision-making.  Provide data-driven insights and optimization recommendations to UX and marketing partners to drive improved consumer experience and conversion.  Execute cross channel analysis to help channel managers and agency improve channel efficiencies.  Coordinate analysis projects with Adobe/Google Analytics and agency teams to produce actionable insights.  Own daily, weekly and ad-hoc Off/Online Channels performance reporting.  Execute analyses that can generate valuable insights and improve performance – cross channel analysis, profitability analysis.  Help with identifying key performance metrics, building dashboards, contributing to key insights and ensuring data driven actions to improve the business.  Work with the agency and web-analytics team to identify ways to improve business reporting capabilities Cross Channel Attribution Analysis.  Identify trends within the consumer journey and create compelling testing (A/B & Multivariate) opportunities to improve experience, conversion and order value across the ecommerce channel.  Own all stages of marketing planning, budgeting and forecasting processes.  Collaborate to facilitate collective understanding of key performance drivers and deliver data driven insights to inform business decisions. Who is Recruiting from Scratch:      Recruiting from Scratch is a premier talent firm that focuses on placing the best product managers, software, and hardware talent at innovative companies. Our team is 100% remote and we work with teams across the United States to help them hire. We work with companies funded by the best investors including Sequoia Capital, Lightspeed Ventures, Tiger Global Management, A16Z, Accel, DFJ, and more.      If you are a fit, the team will reach out to you about this role or any others that may be a fit for our clients.      Our Client      Our client started with an observation: In a world full of applications, why do documents and spreadsheets still run everything? And why haven't they been meaningfully updated in over 50 years? Their product is a new doc that's familiar and flexible like the documents you're used to, but comes with building blocks you can combine to create docs as powerful as apps. It's a big product with an even bigger mission. And they need your help to spread the word! They are backed by some of the Valley's leading venture capitalists, and have assembled a world-class team across offices in San Francisco, Mountain View, and Seattle, and remote employees all over the US. In fact, all their jobs are open in any location across the US. Here's a quick overview of what they do.            Role Overview                       As a growth engineer, you will increase our user base, their usage of the product, and their retention. You will work on features from SEO/SEM for lead generation, incentives for users to upgrade to our paid plans, new user experience, and retention. You will work with a stellar team of passionate, experienced engineers, data scientists, and product managers who have been instrumental in building some of the most widely-used technology products in the world, including YouTube, Google Drive/Docs, Google Shopping/Travel, Amazon AWS, Pinterest, and Microsoft Azure. You will report to one of three managers on our small, close-knit teams.                   Their application runs on React, TypeScript, Python, NodeJS, and sklearn and runs on Kubernetes in Amazon AWS. Their data stack uses Snowflake and Mode Analytics for dashboards. Our client believes in using the best tool for the job and don't shy away from solving complex problems!                       You will:               Work with the product, data, sales, content, and marketing teams to increase growth in users, usage, and retention         Work in a collaborative environment across multiple geo-located offices (Seattle, San Francisco, and Mountain View). Like many of our engineers, you can also work remotely         Help ensure our customers have an excellent experience finding, understanding, and using Coda         Participate in the engineering teams' on-call rotations for customer support and live production issues                        You have:               You have 2+ years of industry experience in a software engineering role and have a software engineering degree or equivalent experience         You have experience in growth engineering, SEO/SEM, A/B testing, and machine learning         You can process complex information, and dive into any part of our systems to promote growth         You are motivated and excel when challenged                                       Benefits                        Medical, Dental, Vision and Life Insurance          401k          Optional Remote or in-office work          Commuter Benefits          Cell & Internet Subsidy          Lunch Subsidy          Fitness Subsidy          Parental Leave          Annual Educational Stipend                             Base Salary Range:  $100,000 to $200,000

POSITION OVERVIEW  A rapidly growing, entrepreneurial technology company, Alarm.com is seeking a Program Lead to join the Alarm.com Training Team to oversee our technical, internal, onboarding program in our call center. The ideal candidate is well versed in technology, well-spoken and enthusiastic, enjoys building relationships, and excels in an ever-changing environment. The role is responsible for the entire learner journey after corporate training for our technical support staff who primarily deliver phone and written support to our product installation partners in our call center. To succeed in this role you will need to be agile and have the ability to communicate across teams who have various levels of familiarity with the program.  By working with a variety of stakeholders including: subject matter experts, instructional designers, content developers, training facilitators, call coaches, quality assurance and department management you'll identify what makes a successful support staff team member and outline the learner onboarding objectives to create an experience which match these ideal outcomes. As a leader, you should be motivated by the desire to optimize productivity by owning each aspect of the process and advising other departments which support the learner on how they can also contribute to the success of the objectives. You will be very hands on with the program to ensure content that is being created and delivered is being received as intended by the learners.  RESPONSIBILITIES   Develop long-term program goals which uphold the organizational standards of satisfaction, quality and performance. Adjust goals to meet the strategic direction of the organization  Work closely with project sponsors, cross-functional teams, and stakeholders to plan and develop scope, deliverables, required resources and timing for new initiatives  Oversee project work and manage project teams for optimal return-on-investment and coordinate / delegate project initiatives  Monitor performance related to project work assigned  Work with invested parties to identify requirements, risks, opportunities and potential hurtles to include in project plans  Oversee and maintain program documentation including procedures. Develop an operating plan and audit cycle  Meet with stakeholders to discuss program status and goals. Present to various audiences and cater program content to be relevant for them  Manage competing resources and priorities while designing content that meets business goals and shapes the learner experience  Communicate project status, issues and decisions in an easy and transparent format  Use evaluation methods to properly review and assess program outcomes to determine any areas of improvement or ways to improve efficiency  Develop action plans to implement change based on identified trends and system improvements  Build, analyze and evaluate program reporting that tracks key program outcomes. Share with relevant stakeholders in a comprehensive way  Stay current on the latest processes and software used by the organization  Be a subject matter expert in the Alarm.com platform, partner tools, hardware and supporting technology  Facilitate and deliver learning content as needed   REQUIREMENTS   Conflict resolution and problem-solving skills  Ability to schedule and manage time/ tasks effectively  Written and verbal communication  Teamwork and motivational skills  Facilitation and training delivery: Superior presentation skills  Ability to work positively with a wide range of individuals  Ability to influence stakeholders and work closely with them to determine acceptable solutions  Delegate work based on support team's skills, talents and availability  Implement change management initiatives and create follow-through to ensure there is alignment with relevant stakeholders  Analyze risk and mitigate unforeseen project roadblocks  Test systems functionality in conjunction with project work   QUALIFIACTIONS 4+ years of experience in training/facilitation  Works effectively in a fast paced, dynamic environment, across departments  Effectively deals with ambiguity and takes action without every detail present  Experience with Learning Management Systems and Webinar Platforms  Experience with designing training programs and curriculums  Well versed in instructional design, training methodologies, and competency assessment   WHY WORK FOR ALARM.COM?   Collaborate with outstanding people : We hire only the best. Our quality standards are high, and our employees enjoy working alongside other high achievers.  Make an immediate impact : New employees can expect to be given responsibility for bringing new technologies to the marketplace within weeks. job_title: Web Developer and Data Visualization Specialist
job_Description: Web Developer and Data Visualization Specialist      Toole Design Group in Minneapolis, MN is looking to hire an experienced and talented full-time  Web Developer and Data Visualization Specialist.  Do you have a strong track record of building visually compelling and narrative-driven web-tools? Are you passionate about creating online tools and interactive platforms? Are you inspired by the power of a well-designed online tool to grab people's attention, teach them something new, or enable them to share their thoughts? Are you interested in developing easy-to-use web-based tools to help agencies better understand mobility patterns? Would you like to work for a firm that is committed to the well-being of its employees? If so, please consider joining our Minneapolis team.      This Web Developer and Data Visualization Specialist position with a focus on interactive webmaps, custom tools and project websites, earns a competitive salary and great benefits, including medical, dental, vision, life insurance, disability, a health savings account (HSA), and a flexible spending account (FSA). We practice what we preach and ensure that our employees also have access to transportation by providing them with financial incentives to bike, walk, or use transit for a better quality of life.      About Toole Design      Toole Design is the leading engineering, planning, and landscape architecture firm specializing in multimodal transportation. Since our start in 2003 as a single office in Maryland, we have expanded throughout the United States and Canada. Our talented team of planners, landscape architects and engineers are committed to delivering quality work that meets the needs of all people, regardless of age, ability, race or gender. We have been named a "best firm to work for" and have one of the lowest staff turnover rates in the industry.      Every project our employees deliver directly and positively affects our communities. We are industry-leading experts, and we work hard to encourage a collaborative and team-oriented environment.      A Day in the Life of a Web Developer and Data Visualization Specialist      You are at the forefront of brainstorming creative solutions for challenging projects. You will work with data scientists, graphic designers, and visualization specialists on active and multimodal transportation projects across North America. You will help develop interactive web maps and surveys for online engagement, custom tools supporting spatial analysis, and project websites to help improve transportation safety and create more travel choices for people of all ages, backgrounds, and abilities. You will work with project managers to meet the unique project needs, budgets, and schedules. You will refine and stretch our capabilities in new directions, building, improving and replacing an existing code base. Project types include bicycle and pedestrian master plans, trail feasibility studies, corridor plans, crash analyses, vision zero safety plans, and other large-scale planning and design efforts. Some examples of our existing products: Safe Street Priority Finder, and the Go Lowell Online Map.      Your job can sometimes be challenging, but you get to work with a close-knit team that is passionate about the work and the communities that you serve.      Qualifications of a Web Developer and Data Visualization Specialist:           3+ years of professional experience developing websites, progressive webapplications, and online tools       A Bachelor's Degree in Geography, GIS, Computer Science, Urban Planning or arelated field; additional experience accepted in lieu of a degree       Proven experience of building websites used by the public       Proven experience building interactive webmaps and interactive data visualizations       Provenexperience with a variety of programming languages, including JavaScript, HTML, CSS, etc.       Experience with one of the following web frameworks: React, Vue, Node, or Django.       Proven experience with a variety of platforms, including Leaflet, ArcGIS Online, Mapbox, and Google Cloud Platform       Knowledge of standard planning and engineering data types and formats, including but not limited to:              GIS network data (including OpenStreetMap)         Time-series data         GPS data                It would be a plus if you have any of the following skills:           Understanding of transportation planning terms, methods, and analyses       Professional experience making accessible and ADA compliant websites, web applications, web maps, and online tools       Python (Matplotlib, seaborn, network osmnx, Django)       PostgreSQL/PostGIS       QGIS       R (ggplot, shiny, igraph)       JavaScript libraries for data visualization, including (D3, Highcharts, Charts, H3)       Cloud hosting and computing platforms (AWS, EC2)       Statistical analysis and/or machine learning       Graphic Design       Mobile development and responsive design          You'll be great here if:           You have experience developing online tools including interactive web maps, dashboards, data visualizations, websites, and analytical tools.       You have experience with online mapping, cartography, and geospatial data.       You have a personal or professional interest in transportation, urban planning, walking, biking, public transit, geography, accessibility, or sustainability.       You are passionate about centering equity in your work       You have strong leadership skills and enjoy participating in multi-disciplinary teams       You are passionate about sustainability and the opportunity to work on challenging multimodal projects that make communities more livable       You enjoy producing high-quality work products and seeing your projects get built       You have strong communication skills, whether written, verbal, or graphically       You can build relationships, bring enthusiasm to exciting projects, and are detail oriented with strong problem-solving skills.                Work Schedule for a Web Developer and Data Visualization Specialist:      This full-time position typically works a flexible schedule of 40 hours a week. We also provide employees with the flexibility and necessary equipment to work from home 2-3 days per week.      About our Minneapolis office:      Toole Design's Minneapolis office is conveniently located downtown at 212 3rd Avenue N, near to the Mississippi River and Cedar Lake bike trail systems and walking distance from Metro Blue, Green, Orange, and C line Stations. The office is easily accessed on foot, by bicycle, and via transit.      Located in the North Loop neighborhood in the historic Colonial Warehouse building, the office is inside the former headquarters of the city's streetcar company. Our windows overlook the Cedar Lake Trail which most of our staff use to bike to work each day, sometimes with a canine in tow (our building is dog-friendly). You will also find Minneapolis staff conducting "walking meetings" to the nearby Mississippi River, taking transit nearly anywhere in the region, or hopping on bike share to attend meetings. Our Minneapolis team is known for its collaborative engineers, planners, landscape architects, and urban designers who are committed to a culture of innovation, excellence, and fun.      Ready to Join our Minneapolis Team?  We understand your time is valuable, so we have a quick and easy application process. If you feel that you would be right for this Web Developer and Data Visualization Specialist position, please fill out our application by clicking on the link on this page.      At Toole Design, diversity is a necessity, not a nice-to-have. We have a collaborative culture where people of all backgrounds come together to share ideas and build better, more inclusive communities. We encourage those from underrepresented communities - women, people of color, LGBTQIA+, immigrants, those with disabilities and people at all the intersections in between - to apply. Even if you don't think your current skill set checks every box below, but this role seems to align with your strengths, we want to hear from you.      We're proud that about half of our managers are women and we are committed to achieving racial diversity in our leadership as well. Toole Design is a woman-owned business and an equal opportunity employer (EO/AA/VEV/Disabled employer).      For more information about Toole Design, visit our website, follow us on Twitter and LinkedIn, or like us on Facebook.

You understand the docker ecosystem and have used it to build and deploy containers in both development and production environments, preferably using ECS.         You are security minded  . You know how to manage secrets in a cloud environment with tools such as AWS param store and Hashicorp vault. You know how to secure a database and you understand common auth protocols such as OAuth/OIDC.         CI/CD pipelines excite you  . You know what makes a CI/CD pipeline successful. theory  Conduct differential item functioning analyses  Link and equate various instruments, scales, tests, assessments, etc.  Contribute to discussions on research design, test/assessment/survey/etc. development, and validity and reliability  Provide statistical consultation for other teams internally  Work with the research and development team on planning and conducting research  Work closely with the research and development team consisting e.g. of psychometricians and psychologists as well as the data science team  Keep abreast of research and developments in psychometrics   YOUR properties of assessments, tests, and/or surveys, and translating data into actionable insights  Extensive knowledge in classical test theory and item response theory (IRT)  Working knowledge of item (e.g., exploratory factor analysis, confirmatory factor analysis, and structural equation modeling)  Familiarity and/or working knowledge of various statistical and IRT software packages (e.g., R, SPSS, Python, Mplus, SAS, PARSCALE, flexMIRT, WINSTEPS, etc.)  Familiarity with computerized adaptive testing, multistage adaptive testing, and automated test assembly  Familiarity with cognitive diagnostic modeling  An analytical approach and excellent attention to detail  A deep fascination for understanding the human experience  Competitive spirit and a clear drive for results  Technical aptitude to master a complex, data-oriented product  Excellent written / oral communication and presentation skills  Independent, organized yet flexible, and able to prioritize work effectively  Highly coachable and motivated by continuous learning with a healthy dose of curiosity and a strong bias for action  Effective collaborator and influencer in a "win as a team" environment   WHAT WE Company Description    Smart People Smart Ideas Smart Choice     A thriving environment for learning, innovation and growth.     Why do so many people join MTS Systems Corporation and stay for a career? Because this is a place where you get to apply your creativity, work with smart people on fascinating projects, and make a positive impact on people’s lives. It is a place where you can learn, innovate and grow professionally.     Transforming what’s possible with cars, aircraft, bridges, wind turbines and space-age materials — this is work we dream about as kids. At MTS, it’s a rewarding career path for talented individuals who are willing to work hard, think hard, and commit to solving complex and critical challenges for our customers around the world, many of whom are leaders in their respective industries.     By joining MTS, you’ll have access to the latest tools and technologies, along with the support of colleagues who are passionate about their work. You’ll discover a dynamic culture of continuous improvement that extends to our people, one that offers numerous ways to expand your knowledge and advance your career. And because we are a global company, your work may also include world travel.           Job Description    MTS is seeking an experienced Lead Software Test Engineer. The Software Test Engineer is a member of the application Software Development Team. The team is responsible for the design, creation, test and continual improvement of MTS application software focused on high performance simulation, analysis and motion control. The Software Test Lead is responsible for Functional Regression, Integration and Acceptance test planning and execution. Ideally will have collaborative work style and have the ability to oversee projects successfully.     Primary Objective:     To plan, coordinate and execute the testing strategy for the product.     Major Areas of Accountability:     1. Coordinate testing effort. Define the time estimates for each test phase and create a schedule. Provide work direction to test engineers participating in the testing. Train test engineers on equipment and test methods. Work with management to solicit internal users as testing resources when required.     2. Create the test strategy and test plan. Maintain process and procedures consistent with overall MTS testing philosophy.     3. Represent test/quality with management. Provide feedback on testing status. Generate reports, track metrics, and create post-release summary.     4. Design and generate high quality, cost effective test cases. Execute test cases using black box techniques and automated testing where applicable. Record and track defects.     5. Manage the testing environment. Keep the lab up-to-date with test machines and hardware needed to support the testing effort. Maintain an effective and current image management system for the test lab.     6. Support product development by participating in requirement and design reviews to ensure the specifications are testable and meet our quality standards.     7. Evaluate software changes for impact on testing, ensuring that effort is made to minimize cost of change.     8. Archive and organize test results and artifacts using configuration management tools.     9. Keep current with advances in test practices and methodologies.     10. Act as a liaison with technical support to provide assistance to internal and external customers.     11. Practice continuous process improvement for opportunities to improve the quality of the test process, including reduction of costs and improved efficiency           Qualifications    Bachelor's Degree in Engineering & 5 years progressively demanding software test experience or AA (vo-tech) deg. in a technical field & 9 years relevant technical exp. or 13 years relevant technical experience.     Solid knowledge of the domain of SW Test/ Development     Demonstrated leadership experience as a Test Lead or other leadership role.     #LI-CR     IND123     Additional Information    All your information will be kept confidential according to EEO guidelines. job_Description: At Shutterfly, we’re all about people — bringing them together, making them feel welcome, and connecting them to experiences. Based in Haifa, and reporting to the VP Engineering in the US, you will build AI/ML and Deep Learning-focused Global Technology Center of Excellence for Shutterfly and Snapfish businesses to use billions of photos and petabytes of data to guide Personalization across consumer touch points on the live website, mobile apps and offsite channels such as emails. You are customer-centric and be willing to take on bold challenges to achieve phenomenal customer experience and business growth through innovation. You will not only double-down on photo-centric personalization but apply Machine Learning expertise to lead the charter on personalizing entire consumer journey ranging from product discovery, automating personalized product creation, and overall shopping experience across all channels and devices.     As an engineering expert and important partner in Shutterfly's product and technology organization, you will identify strategic opportunities and grow an outstanding team of ML and Deep Learning Platform, Big Data, Web and Mobile engineers. With your software engineering and scalable distributed systems background as well as your deep knowledge in machine learning, you will lead machine learning teams and full stack engineering teams to develop custom DL/ML models, SDKs and services that allow these models to be used in low-latency scenarios on web, mobile and server-side that create personalized experiences for our customers. You will work with peer engineering and product teams to ship and operate services at scale and shape the direction of the technology organization in the machine learning space.     You Will:         Operate as an expert with the ability to guide and inspire best performance, innovation and adoption of the latest engineering practices to promote AI, ML and DL technologies across consumer touch points focused on Personalization.      Develop a collaborative and inclusive team that fosters a culture of ownership, experimentation and new ideas to prioritize the things to have the biggest impact on both users and the businesses and provide working solutions for our customers.      Lead an outstanding team of machine learning, big data and full-stack engineers that provide creative, strategic AI-enabled solutions with industry-leading skills in distributed machine learning training workflows, edge AI, data engineering and tools both in the cloud and on-device.      Collaborate with engineering and product teams across the globe to architect and build data ingestion systems and model training pipelines from experimentation to deployment, monitoring and ongoing performance improvement.      Bring your industry expertise and distributed system architecture skills and work with your teams to build high-throughput machine learning training pipelines and low-latency model hosting technologies both on the server-side and the client side (browsers, iOS and Android).        You have:             10+ years in a leadership/management role with experience building engineering teams.      10+ years of software engineering experience and architecting highly available, scalable and low latency systems for high traffic applications.      5+ years of software engineering experience building, and shipping data science AI enabled products.      Experience with machine learning platforms from major cloud providers (such as AWS). Familiarity with AWS Data Lakes, Analytics & ML Services, Redshift, Athena, and EMR.      Familiarity with optimizing ML pipelines to run on-device with constrained compute, power and latency budgets.      Experience diving deep into system architecture, design, performance metrics, code, test plans, project plans, deployments and operations.      Take full ownership of the product from an engineering perspective by authoring a technical vision that aligns with the evolving needs of the organization.      Establish metrics, targets and governance processes to ensure development delivers against success criteria such as scope, schedule, resources, and budget.      Partner with different areas of the business to understand customer needs, and improve support experience, and ensure product is being built in a way that is scalable, sustainable and reliable.      Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Physics, Mathematics or an equivalent technical field.        Our Benefits:         Comprehensive benefits plans      Positive culture with fun and engaged teams

The Opportunity  We are looking for a talented UX Designer or Sr. UX Designer to help our vision in the Ivanti Neurons space. Ivanti's Neurons portfolio includes solutions for Neurons Discovery, Neurons for Healing, Edge Intelligence, Neurons Workspace, Neurons Platform and the Employee Experience product. By leveraging AI and Machine Learning, our Neurons solutions transform the experience of our customers' employees across all areas of the enterprise.  You will help to define and shape the user experience of our Neurons Platform products in close collaboration with product and technical leaders and teams, along with your UX peers in our global UX organization. You will also have the opportunity to bring in new innovations and experiences to our large customer base covering a wide range of different industries and verticals.  Ivanti is investing heavily in UX and has taken big strides towards implementing research and validation practices at scale across our product development teams. We are laser-focused on delivering better products, and the success of our customers.   What You'll Do   Lead and engage in research and discovery activities to develop deep empathy with our customers and understand their needs and challenges. Produce and communicate user personas, user journeys, user flows.  Conduct and facilitate research workshops and sessions in collaboration with user researchers, product leaders, and UX peers.  Design, conduct and communicate research initiatives.  Assist in defining the problems to be addressed and the outcomes we want to create with our products.  Ideate design solutions at all levels of fidelity, from rough whiteboard and paper sketches through to polished visual designs or prototypes when necessary.  Document your designs with well-thought-out use cases, functional specifications for interactions or animations, responsive behaviors, and accessibility standards.  Manage your projects with standard project processes that encourage and grow communication, collaboration and partnerships using collaboration tools like Jira, Confluence, and Teams.  Work closely with product partners to determine UX scope, level of effort, timing and UX deliverables.  Lead the UX testing and validation of your design solutions, iterating and enhancing them in line with the results and feedback obtained.  Work closely with the design systems team to standardize and innovate on components, design patterns, and implementation of the design system.  Mentor and lead other more junior designers on the team.   Experience Required   At least 3-5 years of experience in UX Design with UCD techniques and methodologies in B2C or B2B organizations as in-house design  Portfolio of UX-focused work examples for web and mobile applications   Preferred Qualifications   Bachelor's Degree or master's degree in User Experience, Interaction Design, Human Factors, Psychology, or a related field  Experience with using Jira and Confluence project sites in agile teams  Experience using quantitative reporting tools like Google Tag Manager, Google Analytics, Adobe Analytics  Excellent communication and presentation skills with multiple audience types  Experience designing for Enterprise SaaS applications  Experience working in large UX teams   What We Look For In a Candidate   You are an experienced designer with experience working with Responsive cloud or SaaS products.  You are comfortable playing a leading role in the product design process, guiding a cross-functional team through workshops, design sprints and discovery activities.  You will be able to showcase a strong UX portfolio containing projects that demonstrate the end-to-end process from initial research, through ideation, prototyping and testing, all the way to delivery of the final product.  You will be curious and tenacious in wanting to understand the underlying causes of problems and user behaviors, employing both qualitative and quantitative research techniques to achieve this.  You communicate clearly, confidently, and persuasively, using sound rationale to reinforce your views and decisions, and influence people at all levels.  You instinctively build positive relationships, partnering and collaborating effectively across the wider organization, and multiple geographies.  You demonstrate business acumen and the ability to think strategically.  You lead by example and inspire those around you to do their best work.   Senior Candidates   Contribute strategic design vision and big picture thinking.  Set the bar for other designers in the group.  Advise, support and mentor less experienced members of the team.  Work horizontally across the product teams to drive alignment and consistency, playing a key role in bringing everything together.   Why choose Ivanti?   Join a large, rapidly evolving global UX team of over 20 designers, with plans to grow by 50% within the next 6 months.  Work for a company that is truly invested in UX, where research and discovery work is not only expected, but highly valued.  Leverage and contribute to the development of a world class design system.  Receive support from an established DesignOps team with dedicated front-end resources and soon a dedicated research function.  Embark on a defined career path with real opportunities to grow and advance.  Enjoy a highly competitive salary along with an outstanding benefits package.   #LI-JM1  #Li-REMOTE

The Application Architect is a both a consultative and strategic role within the Cambria IT Product Development team that leads in definition, design, and delivery of diverse software systems based upon documented requirements and our agile development practices. As a consultant, the Application Architect owns the “How?” portion of the solution delivery by working with Product Owners, Developers, and business stakeholders to help identify and describe one or more methods to approach a business problem and drive measurable business outcomes using a variety of tools at their disposal which includes technology, data, and business processes. The Application Architect will also be responsible for establishing and maintaining relationships with other leaders and doers in the organization to ensure Cambria has the right individuals at the table for input and decision making at the start of and throughout the project delivery lifecycle. As a strategist, the Application Architect will be responsible for the output of key project deliverables such as system context diagrams that explain the components, users, and processes involved in a solution, technical design documents that the development teams will use to plan and execute their work, and will work closely with the Product Owners to add important details to user stories or meet with the teams regularly through standups to answer questions, resolve ambiguity, or provide direction in software development lifecycle stages.
